import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Create a bar chart of the distribution of Effect_Amount_of_damage
    chart = sns.countplot(x='Effect_Amount_of_damage', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Effect_Amount_of_damage?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Effect Amount of Damage')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Effect Amount of Damage', loc='upper right', labels=data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    species_count = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=species_count.values, y=species_count.index, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Wildlife Species')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Wildlife_Species?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    phase_counts = data['Phase_of_flight'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(phase_counts, labels=phase_counts.index, autopct='%.2f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Phase_of_flight?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Speed_IAS_in_knots', kde=True, bins=20)
    median_speed = data['Speed_IAS_in_knots'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_speed, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_speed:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Speed_IAS_in_knots?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
